<figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="fig_1"><head>Figure 1</head><label>1</label><figDesc>Figure 1 summarises the structural features of the photo-switching process of BBCP from the reactant to the product state as been derived from the crystallographic data (monomer: R1 = 0.0426 (11722 unique Bragg reflections), wR2 = 0.1242, GooF= 1.842, ca. 45000 reflections in total, dimer: R1 = 0.0495 (9834 unique Bragg reflections), wR2 = 0.1394, GooF = 1.675, spatial resolution: d = 0.6 Å). The x-ray diffraction patterns were analyzed by the use of the software package SHELXTL.</figDesc><graphic coords="1,237.78,491.04,173.71,91.92" type="bitmap" /></figure>
